      "message": "I took a look at this and found that for my use case, what I really wanted was a `equal_pixel` just comparing two colors with a tolerance. (I only have one Bitmap, and changing the test to require a second Bitmap just so I could call `equal_pixels` felt like the cart leading the horse.)\n\nI did update `equal_pixels` to support a tolerance value (using repeated calls to `equal_pixel`), but we don\u0027t actually use that functionality anywhere. I can land that part of it or not, your call. It won\u0027t be very fast since it decodes each pixel individually, but I couldn\u0027t justify optimizing a path we don\u0027t use :) ",
